Show HN: Easiest way to build live audio and video apps
text:
What do we Solve for?

Day by day, the world is becoming small for everyone with lots of cool applications having native audio/video communications, and interactive live streaming capabilities.

Some of them are helping you to interact with your friends, and colleagues or watching your favourite person live. Building these immersive experiences requires high-quality in-app conferencing and interactive live streaming.

Video SDK solves the same problem. It helps developers to build highly interactive and immersive experiences with our cutting-edge live audio and video SDKs.

Why Video SDK?

We are building the most powerful and reliable SDKs. It has been developed by a developer for developers.

It helps you to build live audio and video interactiveness and engagement on steroids; High-energy collaborative sessions that participants love.

We believe that the future is immersive and building virtual worlds and virtual connections are just getting started.

Video SDK is the first choice of thousands of developers because of

- Cross-platform support for web and mobile devices - Developer-friendly high-level and low-level SDKs & APIs - Scale it to millions of users globally - Customise it as per your need - Compatible with all browsers and devices - Record it, stream it, and save it on your servers - Adaptive streaming with intelligent algorithm - Build collaborative features such as poll, q&a and whiteboard easily

What's next?

Our vision is to make the world immersive and connected with innovative technological improvements in real-time audio and video.

Our team is working hard to build the technology which can scale to millions of people with crystal clear quality audio and video. Hold tight! We are coming up with a product that will change the way we communicate, interact and socialize virtually.

Let us know what you think

We’ve built Video SDK with the love of community from day 1. Even after a year, We are delighted to have feedback and suggestions from 1200+ community members on making it better.

We believe that it’s just again day one for us and we want your genuine feedback and suggestions on what we have been building.

And I would really appreciate your support, let us know your valuable feedback and suggestions in the comments.

Ask HN: What is the best config file documentation you have seen?
text:
I run a project called goreleaser, which is configurable via YAML.

Since it has a lot of options, it can get confusing. I do provide a JSONSchema and a documentation page, with all available options and some commented examples.

Still, I feel like it could be better - especially regarding informing in which version a given option was added, discoverability, etc.. I'm just not sure how to make it so.

That said, I wonder: what is the best software configuration documentation you have ever seen?
